From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Krzysztof Kozlowski <krzysztof.kozlowski@linaro.org>
Date: Thu, 23 Oct 2025 12:45:52 +0200
Subject: arm64: qcom_laptops.config: Enable SECURITY_LANDLOCK

CONFIG_SECURITY_LANDLOCK is needed on Ubuntu by localsearch ("Tracker
file system data miner") service for file indexing:

  localsearch-3[72620]: Refusing to extract file data since Landlock could not be enabled. Update your kernel to fix this warning.
  localsearch-3[72620]: Could not get landlock supported ABI: Function not implemented

Signed-off-by: Krzysztof Kozlowski <krzysztof.kozlowski@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
index ea1be4d4913a..babfe278f62c 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_laptops.config
@@ -65,6 +65,8 @@ CONFIG_SQUASHFS_XATTR=y
 CONFIG_SQUASHFS_LZ4=y
 CONFIG_SQUASHFS_LZO=y
 CONFIG_SQUASHFS_XZ=y
+# For Ubuntu/localsearch
+CONFIG_SECURITY_LANDLOCK=y
 
 # For network sharing, e.g. in Ubuntu connection sharing with test boards
 CONFIG_IP_ADVANCED_ROUTER=y
-- 
2.53.0

